# Privacy Policy for ResQZone

**Last Updated: November 19, 2025**

## Introduction

ResQZone ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application ResQZone (the "App").

Please read this privacy policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this privacy policy, please do not access the application.

## Information We Collect

### Personal Information
When you register and use ResQZone, we collect the following personal information:

- **Name**: To identify users and rescuers
- **Email Address**: For account authentication and communication
- **Phone Number**: For contact purposes and emergency communication
- **Location Data**: GPS coordinates to match users with nearby rescuers
- **City, State, and Country**: Derived from your location for display purposes
- **Profile Photo**: If you choose to upload one
- **Role**: Whether you are a user or rescuer
- **Animal Category**: If you are a rescuer (e.g., Dogs, Birds, Reptiles, Wild Animals)

### Report Information
When you submit an animal rescue report, we collect:

- **Animal Photos**: Images you capture or upload
- **Location**: GPS coordinates where the animal was found
- **Description**: Details about the animal and situation
- **Category**: Type of animal requiring rescue
- **Timestamp**: Date and time of report submission

### Automatically Collected Information
We automatically collect certain information when you use the App:

- **Device Information**: Device type, operating system, unique device identifiers
- **Log Data**: IP address, app features used, time and date of access
- **Firebase Analytics**: Anonymous usage statistics to improve app performance

## How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information for the following purposes:

1. **Service Delivery**
   - Connect users with nearby rescuers based on location and animal category
   - Display rescue reports to appropriate rescuers within a 15km radius
   - Enable communication between users and rescuers

2. **Communication**
   - Send notifications about rescue status updates
   - Notify rescuers of new reports in their area
   - Send important updates about the service

3. **App Improvement**
   - Analyze usage patterns to improve features
   - Fix bugs and technical issues
   - Enhance user experience

4. **Safety and Security**
   - Verify user identities
   - Prevent fraudulent activities
   - Ensure compliance with terms of service

## Data Storage and Security

### Firebase Services
Your data is stored using Google Firebase services:

- **Firebase Authentication**: Securely stores user credentials
- **Cloud Firestore**: Stores user profiles and rescue reports
- **Firebase Storage**: Stores uploaded images
- **Firebase Cloud Messaging**: Handles push notifications

### Security Measures
We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data:

- Industry-standard encryption for data transmission
- Secure Firebase authentication
- Regular security updates and monitoring
- Access controls and user authentication

However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

## Data Sharing and Disclosure

### With Other Users
- Your **name, contact number, email, and location (city/state)** are visible to rescuers when you submit a report
- Rescuers can see your **contact information** to coordinate rescue efforts
- Your **rescue reports** including photos and descriptions are visible to matching rescuers

### With Service Providers
We may share your information with third-party service providers:
- **Google Firebase**: Cloud hosting and database services
- **Google Maps**: Location services and mapping

### Legal Requirements
We may disclose your information if required to:
- Comply with legal obligations
- Protect and defend our rights or property
- Prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing
- Protect personal safety of users or the public

## Your Data Rights

You have the following rights regarding your personal data:

### Access and Update
- You can view and update your profile information in the app drawer
- Access your submitted reports in the "My Reports" section

### Deletion
- You can request deletion of your account and associated data by contacting us
- Deleted data will be removed from our active databases within 30 days
- Some data may be retained for legal compliance purposes

### Opt-Out
- You can disable location services in your device settings (this will limit app functionality)
- You can disable push notifications in app settings

## Location Data

ResQZone uses location data to:
- Match users with nearby rescuers (within 15km radius)
- Display your city and state in your profile
- Show the location of reported animals to rescuers

Location data is collected only when:
- You register for an account
- You submit a rescue report
- You log into the app

You can revoke location permissions in your device settings, but this will prevent you from using core app features.

## Children's Privacy

ResQZone is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you become aware that a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will take steps to delete such information.

## Push Notifications

We use Firebase Cloud Messaging to send push notifications:
- When a rescuer accepts your report
- When new reports are available in your area (for rescuers)

You can disable notifications in your device settings or by denying notification permissions when prompted.

## Data Retention

We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to:
- Provide our services
- Comply with legal obligations
- Resolve disputes
- Enforce our agreements

When you delete your account, we will delete or anonymize your personal data within 30 days, except where retention is required by law.

## Third-Party Links

The App may contain links to third-party websites or services (such as email clients or phone dialers) that are not operated by us. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by:
- Updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy
- Posting the new policy in the app
- Sending a notification through the app (for material changes)

Your continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

## International Data Transfers

Your information may be transferred to and maintained on servers located outside your country. By using ResQZone, you consent to the transfer of information to countries outside your country of residence, which may have different data protection rules.

## Contact Us

If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:

**Email**: dhananjay7781@gmail.com
**GitHub**: https://github.com/dhananjay7781/ResQZone

## Your Consent

By using ResQZone, you consent to:
- The collection and use of information as described in this Privacy Policy
- The storage of your data on Firebase servers
- The sharing of your contact information with rescuers for coordination purposes

## California Privacy Rights (CCPA)

If you are a California resident, you have additional rights:
- Right to know what personal information is collected
- Right to know if personal information is sold or disclosed
- Right to delete personal information
- Right to opt-out of the sale of personal information (we do not sell data)
- Right to non-discrimination for exercising your rights

## GDPR Rights (European Users)

If you are in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have rights under GDPR:
- Right of access to your personal data
- Right to rectification of inaccurate data
- Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")
- Right to restrict processing
- Right to data portability
- Right to object to processing
- Right to withdraw consent

